Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.89,0:00:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,June 19th.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.06,0:00:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I met with Franz Bonaparta for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.73,0:00:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,R.F. 17 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.39,0:00:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man with a quiet and calm demeanor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.65,0:00:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A refined and aristocratic look.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.44,0:00:25.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dressed in a suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.19,0:00:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.11,0:00:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the children gathered for a book reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.83,0:00:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you want to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.75,0:00:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The border.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.96,0:00:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.29,0:00:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Czech border.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.75,0:00:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.92,0:00:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.64,0:01:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the afternoon, the children gathered for a book reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.40,0:01:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A very strange mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.73,0:01:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.44,0:01:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P. Brevnov W.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.95,0:01:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A spire on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.86,0:01:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A weather vane on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.70,0:01:15.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Human dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.54,0:01:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.25,0:01:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A wonderful experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.54,0:01:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The deprivation of dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.04,0:01:22.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What country are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.79,0:01:25.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I asked where you're from.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.00,0:01:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.51,0:01:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if a Japanese person would like this, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.80,0:01:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.89,0:01:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's left over from my lunch, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.01,0:01:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.35,0:01:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.81,0:01:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just eat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.39,0:01:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look like you're gonna collapse any second now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.40,0:01:48.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My wife keeps nagging at me to lose some weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.49,0:01:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.40,0:01:51.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, eat up!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.28,0:01:55.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't, you won't make it through the long journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.21,0:02:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to end this journey already...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.28,0:03:36.95,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(367,0)\pos(362,356)}The Unending Journey
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:36.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.34,0:03:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You let him go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.05,0:03:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just let Tenma leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.35,0:03:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.97,0:03:44.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you stop him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.81,0:03:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You already know he's a man you can't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.85,0:03:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.11,0:03:51.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On top of which...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.40,0:03:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we're in a dire situation with Eva Heinemann missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:03:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma even escaped from jail because of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.91,0:04:10.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That lawyer who called himself Baul...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.08,0:04:14.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's most likely the same man who\Ntried to kill me at my clinic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.76,0:04:17.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His objective was to get close to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.97,0:04:20.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and obtain my father's notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.43,0:04:25.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those notes must be very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.02,0:04:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.52,0:04:27.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.10,0:04:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To where Tenma is headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.23,0:04:32.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "Red Rose Mansion"?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.61,0:04:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.15,0:04:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father's notes were full of meaningless descriptions...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.86,0:04:40.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I don't think they were written in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.45,0:04:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.45,0:04:45.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P. Brevnov W.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.91,0:04:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,P is for Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.79,0:04:49.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W means west.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.79,0:04:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A suburb of Prague, west of Brevnov!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.25,0:04:54.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A place where you can see "a spire on the left..."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.80,0:04:57.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"and a weather vane on the right."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.17,0:04:59.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.59,0:05:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just hope there's an eyewitness or someone who\Ncan help us solve the case at that mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.81,0:05:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's unlikely now...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.69,0:05:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.94,0:05:15.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"In the afternoon, the children\Ngathered for a book reading."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.98,0:05:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was described in the notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.49,0:05:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The children from back then could be our witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.03,0:05:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Verdeman.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.91,0:05:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I blamed you for letting Tenma go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.37,0:05:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if I had been in that situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.54,0:05:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I would've done the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.00,0:05:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.43,0:05:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.85,0:05:47.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to live in this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.73,0:05:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.98,0:05:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Welcome home.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.24,0:06:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Nina?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.62,0:06:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.54,0:06:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's better if we give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.00,0:06:15.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many times we do this, we still get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.38,0:06:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm sure I'll remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.34,0:06:22.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back then, my brother told me what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.47,0:06:25.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How he was taken away from The Three Frogs...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.05,0:06:28.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What he passed, and where he went.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.31,0:06:30.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He went past the train station...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.68,0:06:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and while he was watching the town on his left...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.68,0:06:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a trolley followed him along the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.78,0:06:44.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please turn right over...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.66,0:06:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You shouldn't.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.37,0:06:51.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You shouldn't hide anything from him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:06:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.21,0:07:00.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.63,0:07:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,l-lt's nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.93,0:07:10.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.97,0:07:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you recognize any landmarks?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.35,0:07:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.65,0:07:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.82,0:07:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't remember something from so long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.61,0:07:26.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.23,0:08:02.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A weather vane on the right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.33,0:08:14.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A church spire on the left...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.95,0:08:16.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.06,0:08:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Red Rose Mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.20,0:08:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the place?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.91,0:08:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.58,0:08:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.50,0:08:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.84,0:09:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.52,0:09:27.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.20,0:09:41.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like a door just appeared from inside the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.29,0:10:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.66,0:10:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.38,0:10:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.84,0:10:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You devil!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.34,0:10:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You devil!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.98,0:10:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The devil has been slain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.84,0:11:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.26,0:11:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back, Mr. Lipsky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.72,0:11:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get any customers?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.73,0:11:30.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, business was as bad as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.06,0:11:32.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the puppets are all so wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.65,0:11:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one I'm making now is even better.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.12,0:11:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.20,0:11:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once I finish, you'll be the first to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.91,0:11:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for me to go to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.21,0:11:51.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.21,0:11:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I can't earn a living on just the puppets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.17,0:11:58.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry for imposing on you for so long...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.88,0:12:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.13,0:12:01.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.14,0:12:07.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Lipsky, there's something I want to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.02,0:12:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.89,0:12:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.44,0:12:15.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you found me after I collapsed\Nand took me to a hospital...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.27,0:12:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.94,0:12:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why were you at that mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.28,0:12:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nina?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.41,0:12:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nina?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.62,0:12:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nina!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.62,0:12:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Answer me, Nina?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.04,0:12:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nina!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.16,0:12:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's wrong?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I go to that mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.63,0:12:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,images come to me for my work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.01,0:12:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How should I put it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.47,0:12:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But right now, more than that mansion, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.23,0:12:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.73,0:12:54.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.23,0:12:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can stay here for as long as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.73,0:13:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.31,0:13:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.15,0:13:39.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,O-Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you should be out of bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.78,0:13:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.32,0:13:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.86,0:13:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is where the puppets are bom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.87,0:13:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad I don't have any customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.45,0:13:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of story is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.54,0:13:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the story of a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.34,0:14:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.88,0:14:03.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.93,0:14:08.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A devil who leaves to find the dragon\Nthat threatens to destroy this world...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.93,0:14:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but almost dies in the middle of his journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.73,0:14:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A young man passing by saves his life, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.52,0:14:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the young man learns the true\Nidentity of the one he saved...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.53,0:14:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he goes after the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.32,0:14:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And at the end of his journey, the\Nyoung man finds the devil...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.58,0:14:32.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and with a knife in his hand, slays the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.62,0:14:36.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's an interesting story, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.46,0:14:38.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nobody seems to like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.71,0:14:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Are you okay, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.59,0:14:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I would do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.80,0:14:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.14,0:14:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.22,0:14:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let him do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.64,0:14:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.81,0:14:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you were human...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.11,0:15:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'd save that devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.52,0:15:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.03,0:15:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he'd like this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.61,0:15:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.61,0:15:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On this bookshelf...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.20,0:15:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all picture books.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.91,0:15:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jakub Farobek.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.75,0:15:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.58,0:15:18.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emil Sebe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.59,0:15:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Monster Without a Name."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.71,0:15:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you know of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.01,0:15:29.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wrote many picture books.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.22,0:15:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jakub Farobek.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.93,0:15:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.31,0:15:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emil Sebe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all pen names of the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.40,0:15:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man named Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.48,0:15:46.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Franz... Bonaparta...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.28,0:15:48.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Human beings...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.45,0:15:52.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}can become anything.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.58,0:15:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I wasn't a "superior child"...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.46,0:15:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was driven away from the book readings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.46,0:16:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Book readings?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.00,0:16:08.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His book readings were held at the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.30,0:16:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was a student there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.55,0:16:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understood what he was trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.93,0:16:20.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A deal! Let's make a deal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.10,0:16:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,said the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.44,0:16:25.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"No! Absolutely not!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.69,0:16:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,said the man with big eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.40,0:16:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Yes! Let's make a deal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.66,0:16:33.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,said the man with a big mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.87,0:16:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man with a big mouth's yard became a flower garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.45,0:16:43.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man with big eyes became destitute and starved.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.29,0:16:50.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man with a big mouth was cheerful every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.26,0:16:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was full from all his ripened fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.55,0:16:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is why he did not notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.10,0:16:59.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His flower garden was wilting away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.64,0:17:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the garden where no flower would ever bloom again...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.52,0:17:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the man with a big mouth cried and muttered...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.82,0:17:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I should never have made a deal with the devil."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.20,0:17:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man with big eyes was so hungry\Nthat he thought he would die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.45,0:17:21.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shedding tears, he muttered...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.54,0:17:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I should have made a deal with the devil. "
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.08,0:17:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"A deal! Let's make a deal!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.21,0:17:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,said the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.93,0:17:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Man with Big Eyes, the Man with\Na Big Mouth," by Jakub Farobek.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.89,0:17:42.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each Friday at three o'clock in the afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.77,0:17:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we would gather for the book readings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.94,0:17:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We would sit around him...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.44,0:17:51.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and listen as he read us a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.82,0:17:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With his kind voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.86,0:17:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A very calm and kind voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.99,0:18:01.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And when he finished reading a story...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.54,0:18:04.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would ask us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.83,0:18:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The meaning of the story..."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.42,0:18:10.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"do you understand?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.01,0:18:15.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.55,0:18:19.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I also understood after reading it many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.39,0:18:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.39,0:18:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would take another picture book into his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.85,0:18:27.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The God of Peace," by Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.27,0:18:31.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's try reading this next.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.08,0:18:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's as if I've come here for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.41,0:18:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although it took me quite some time...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.50,0:18:51.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all the memories have come together.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.30,0:19:00.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The god of peace is always busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.14,0:19:01.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is too busy to look in a mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.81,0:19:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and blows his horn every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.39,0:19:08.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The god of peace's horn makes everyone happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.94,0:19:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The god of peace is always busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.57,0:19:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is too busy to look in a mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.40,0:19:16.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and scatters magical water.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.07,0:19:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The magical water creates green mountains...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.03,0:19:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ripens crops, and makes flower gardens grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.45,0:19:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The god of peace is always busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.21,0:19:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is too busy to look in a mirror...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.87,0:19:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and gives everyone a name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.04,0:19:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Your name is Otto."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.34,0:19:35.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Your name is Hans."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.72,0:19:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Your name is Thomas."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.47,0:19:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Your name is..."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.51,0:19:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Johan."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.56,0:19:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Johan gave his hat to the god as a gift in return.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.64,0:19:50.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The god was very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.31,0:19:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he wanted to see himself wearing the hat...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.77,0:19:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he stood in front of a mirror for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.15,0:19:58.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.20,0:20:02.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what he saw in the mirror was a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.45,0:20:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The devil spoke to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.62,0:20:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I am you..."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.95,0:20:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"and you are me."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.66,0:20:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Oh, no!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.92,0:20:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"No one can live in peace with a devil like this!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.38,0:20:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"What should I do?"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.63,0:20:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, the troubled god...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.97,0:20:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what he did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.76,0:20:24.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.56,0:20:27.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.14,0:20:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what the "god" did after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.48,0:20:34.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.24,0:20:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We finally meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.45,0:20:42.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.49,0:20:44.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.28,0:20:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.54,0:20:53.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think even you could have told us apart, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.00,0:20:55.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am her, and she is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.92,0:20:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am you, and you are me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.97,0:21:01.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand everything now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.43,0:21:03.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where we came from...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.68,0:21:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and where we are heading.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.06,0:21:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The weather outside is wonderful, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.20,0:21:29.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let the flames engulf everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.60,0:21:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.81,0:21:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The god...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.87,0:22:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pointed the gun...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.46,0:22:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at his forehead!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.88,0:22:25.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shoot me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.91,0:22:31.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.08,0:22:44.51,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.08,0:22:44.51,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(201,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.51,0:22:47.47,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.47,0:23:01.15,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.47,0:23:01.15,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.75,0:23:26.01,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.01,0:23:34.43,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.43,0:23:36.89,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.83,0:23:54.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
